Paper: hep-th/0002031

Date: 2000-02-04

Title: Confinement and the AdS/CFT Correspondence

Authors: D. S. Berman and Maulik K. Parikh

Comments: 12 pages, 1 figure, RevTeX

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B483 (2000) 271-276

We study the thermodynamics of the confined and unconfined phases ofsuperconformal Yang-Mills in finite volume and at large N using the AdS/CFTcorrespondence. We discuss the necessary conditions for a smooth phasecrossover and obtain an N-dependent curve for the phase boundary.